y using participatory and inclusive approaches and the use of experiential knowledge in its construction. It will challenge traditional state and market-led approaches to welfare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aMedical policy. 0aPublic welfare. 0aSocial policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aAlston, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmaya, Ana B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnett-Cormack, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeresford, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeresford, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBeresford, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlack, Stella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBourlet, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoxall, Kathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrady, Louca-Mai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurdett, Emmeline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurns, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCameron, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaroline,, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Sarah, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCasey, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClark, Colin